# Partrunner Image Generator

App web que genera imágenes editoriales con IA para Partrunner (logística last-mile en México).

## Architecture

- **Frontend:** React 19 + Vite 6 + Tailwind CSS 4 (SPA in `src/`)
- **Backend:** Express server (`server.ts`) with two API routes
- **AI Transform:** Claude Sonnet via Anthropic API (`/api/transform`)
- **AI Image:** Gemini 3 Pro Image Preview via Google AI API (`/api/generate`)
- **Design System:** Partrunner DS — light theme, Inter font, #FFD840 yellow, #14142B black
- **Deploy:** Railway (Express serves built frontend in production)

## Flow

1. User enters simple prompt + selects format (6 options)
2. `/api/transform` sends to Claude → returns editorial JSON
3. `/api/generate` sends `prompt_compiled` to Gemini 3 Pro Image → returns base64 image (2K)
4. Frontend displays image with download option + JSON viewer

## Key files

- `server.ts` — Express backend (both API routes)
- `src/data/brand.ts` — Brand identity, formats, system prompt (HARDCODED)
- `src/types/editorial.ts` — TypeScript interfaces for editorial JSON
- `src/services/api.ts` — Frontend fetch calls to backend
- `src/App.tsx` — Main UI component
- `public/images/` — 7 logo variants (downloaded from Supabase)

## Rules

- API keys NEVER in client code — always through Express backend
- Brand identity is hardcoded in `src/data/brand.ts`, never user-configurable
- System prompt is in `brand.ts` AND duplicated in `server.ts` (server version is authoritative)
- `prompt_compiled` must NEVER include text rendering instructions
- UI follows Partrunner Design System: light theme, #FFD840 yellow, Inter font
- Gemini model: `gemini-3-pro-image-preview` (Nano Banana Pro) via `generateContent`
